news.title: Explain regularisation of illegal residential colonies on pasture land: HC to Rajasthan govt
news.para: ​​In its petition, the Shri Rajasthan Gau Seva Samiti stated the state government had introduced a policy on December 27 last year to regularise encroachments on the pasture land or gochar, which are over 35 years old.

news.title: Mumbai: ED attaches Omkar group's flats at Worli worth Rs 330 crore
news.para: Earlier, the ED had arrested Babulal Varma and Kamal Kishor, managing director and chairman of the Omkar group, respectively, in the case along with Sachin Joshi, promoter of J M Joshi group.

news.title: Telangana government now eyeing housing board land for auctions
news.para: The state government is learnt to have asked the housing board to hand over certain land parcels owned by it to the Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) for holding auctions.

news.title: Kanpur civic body directs staffers to start house tax collection
news.para: Senior KMC officers have directed the zonal officers to start taking measures against tax defaulters and collect tax in order to achieve their targets.

news.title: Chandigarh administrator approves adoption of Model Tenancy Act
news.para: After considering all objections and suggestions from public, the UT administration had recently finalised it and sent the file to Purohit for final approval.

news.title: Pune: 23 merged villages out of gunthewari scheme ambit
news.para: Yuvraj Deshmukh, a senior Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) official, said, “The sanctioning authority for building permissions for the properties in these villages is different. Hence, the civic body will not be able to regularise illegal constructions there.”

news.title: Delhi HC seeks DDA reply on plea over Kalkaji slums demolition
news.para: The petition filed by Santosh Giri and other local residents has challenged the action of DDA of demolishing the slums near Lotus Temple Road, Kalkaji without prior notice. Some jhuggis were demolished last month.

news.title: Waive property tax, charges for one year: FHRAI to Maharashtra CM
news.para: The hospitality industry has estimated business losses totalling Rs 1.4 lakh crore, leaving around 5 crore employees jobless in the country.

news.title: Prima facie, malls don't have rights to collect parking fees: Kerala HC
news.para: ​Justice P V Kunhikrishnan, while hearing a plea that the mall was illegally collecting parking fees from customers, however, did not ask the mall to stop the collection but said it would be at their risk.

news.title: No presumption of innocence for Ansals in Uphaar case: Delhi Police to HC
news.para: Special public prosecutor (SPP) Dayan Krishnan told Justice Subramonium Prasad that the mutilation of "vital documents" forced the prosecution to record the secondary evidence in the case which resulted in an enormous delay of trial court proceedings.

news.title: Three illegal colonies razed by DTCP in Gurugram
news.para: These colonies were developed on 10 acres of land in the residential zone of Sector 93 and in Sector 94, which is an open space zone.

news.title: Maharashtra extends 50% discount in building premiums till January 31
news.para: ​​On Friday, the urban development department issued a notification extending the deadline till January 31.

news.title: India to contribute 37% of the APAC office space demand: Cushman & Wakefield
news.para: Despite the brief uncertainty during the second wave, the office market across the top 8 cities has fared well with a perceptible growth in the market activity, especially in the second half, according to perspective 2022 report by Cushman & Wakefield.

news.title: Google buys office building in London for $1 billion
news.para: Google, which employs 6,400 people in Britain, plans a multi-million pound refurbishment of its offices within the Central Saint Giles development it is buying, close to Covent Garden in central London.

news.title: China Evergrande shares climb after winning bond payment delay
news.para: Struggling with $300 billion in liabilities, including $19 billion in international bonds deemed to be in cross-default after missing a payment deadline last month, Evergrande is working to avoid a technical default onshore that would complicate its politically sensitive restructuring.
